<h2> Definition </h2>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{@EM{{toki}}}} is a noun that indicates the time when something is or was done. It is often translated
as "at the time when".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{hiroshiha@KJ{{test^verification}}no@EM{{toki}}kazewohikimashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Hiroshi caught a cold at exam time.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{teri-}}ha@KT{{ju-su}}ga@KJ{{relax}}i@EM{{toki}}nitakusan @KJ{{buy}}tteoita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Terry bought a lot of juice when it was cheap.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
When the subjects of the clause before @HI{{@EM{{toki}}}} and the main clause differ, the subject of the @HI{{@EM{{toki}}}} clause should be marked by @HI{{ga}} rather than by @HI{{ha}}.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha@KJ{{large^study^life}}no@EM{{toki}},@KJ{{meeting^company}}wotsukutta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      When I was a university student, I formed a company.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ga@KJ{{large^study^life}}no@EM{{toki}},@KJ{{younger*brother}}ha@KJ{{meeting^company}}wotsukutta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      When I was a university student, my younger brother formed a company.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@Vru{{}}@HI{{@EM{{toki}}}} means that the action in the relative clause has not yet completed when the main clause happens.
This can often be translated as <em>right before</em>.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}hago@KJ{{meal}}wo@KJ{{eat}}beru@EM{{toki}}@KJ{{hand}}wo@KJ{{wash}}u.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I will wash my hands right before I eat my meal.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{country}}he@KJ{{homecoming}}ru@EM{{toki}},kabanwo@KJ{{buy}}imashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I bought a bag when I was going back to my country (and I bought it before I finished my journey).
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@Vta{{}}@HI{{@EM{{toki}}}} means that the action in the relative clause has completed when the action in the main clause takes place.
This can often be translated as <em>right after</em>.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}hago@KJ{{meal}}wo@KJ{{eat}}beta@EM{{toki}}@KJ{{hand}}wo@KJ{{wash}}u.}}      
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I will wash my hands right after I eat my meal.      
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{country}}he@KJ{{homecoming}}tta@EM{{toki}},kabanwo@KJ{{buy}}imashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I bought a bag when I went back to my country (after my trip had been completed and I had already arrived in my country).
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

